    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-03-03T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-03-03T02:00:00-05:00" n="687"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d687">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.003/544: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-03-03T15:00:00+08:00"
                            >March 3, 1931—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 4—6:03 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Japanese Chargé, Shigemitsu, has just told me that on February 28 Ambassador
                        Debuchi<note n="41" xml:id="d687fn41">Katsuji Debuchi, Japanese Ambassador
                        in the United States.</note> was informed by Assistant Secretary Castle of
                    the Department’s decision to drop negotiations on extraterritoriality with Dr.
                    C. C. Wu at Washington, owing to dissatisfaction with the Chinese Minister’s
                    attitude, wherefore negotiations had been transferred to China.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
